The paper deals with a communication system that combines MIMO and NOMA techniques to address challenges such as massive connectivity, low latency, and high reliability. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT), Communications (cs.COMM), and Signal Processing (cs.SI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a practical implementation of the system with low complexity, which could fall under the Networked Systems (cs.NI) and Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories.
